text: The COVID-19 pandemic began affecting North Carolina on March 22, 2020. As of May 2021 North Carolina had the 10th highest number of confirmed cases for the United States During the pandemic in North Carolina, almost 5,800 people died from the COVID or its complications. ==References== Category:COVID-19 pandemic in the United States Category:2020s in North Carolina
title: COVID-19 pandemic in North Carolina
